title: For Sale/Trade:  Norinco SKS. Mis-stamped sporter. DB stamp as well.
postcontent:
Collectors grade SKS. 
Located in Evansville, IN but posting here for broader audience. 
All matching Norinco Chinese sks. Sporter version. Non thumbhole stock and does not accept ak mags. Is 100% matching, original and real. Have green sling, cleaning kit that fits in stock, screwdriver type bayonet. Comes with about 700 rounds of various factory ammo (norinco steel core, Winchester, brown bear, golden bear, silver bear, Tula and wolf). I have owned for over 22 years. Less than 500 rounds shot thru it. Well taken care of and pristine condition. Again all numbers match. Is stamped Tucson AZ. Is also a legit DB stamp. Here's the history:

In 1989 sks were stamped sporter or sks-m to be allowed for import after a 1989 ban. These rifles were fitted with Monte Carlo or thumbhole stocks. Also made and adapted to accept ak mags. Also had the bayo lug removed. The rifle I have has had none of the cosmetic changes yet is stamped sporter. Plus it has the DB stamp. That means deport Bangladesh. Some Chinese made sks were stamped this or DP(Pakistan) or DK(Kampuchea). DP typically adds 10% value. DK about 15-20%. And the most rare DB adding up to 50% based on condition. Many DP have been forged to appear DB. They are easy to tell due to the mis proportion of the humps of the B. so the sporter mis-stamp, DB stamp and #'s matching drives it to a collectors rifle.
And when I mention the 1989 ban I don't mean the 1994 awb. The 1989 ban also ban import of norinco ammo which some is included with the rifle. A 20 rnd box of norinco was fetching 35-40 bucks before the paranoia after conn.
Also another change was the bolt carrier was changed on sporters with no slots for striped clips since they used ak removable mags and no stripper clip was needed. 
Most sporters had barrels shortened too. 
Package valued at $1200. 

WILL TRADE FOR:

S&W 629 stealth hunter 44 mag od green
Ar 15 50 beawulf or 223 or 338 lapua
Other handguns in 45, 9mm or 10mm
Make offer

Brand new, never fired Glock 19 Gen 4.
Recently purchased (27FEB2013).
Original case and 3 - 15 round mags.
Production date: January 2013.
Has correct ejector 30274 and RSA 0-4-3.
Bought it at store, took it home, and sitting in vault.
Cash value is $650 but it is not for sale - TRADE ONLY.

Want to trade only for:

Glock 17 Gen 4.
Must come with original case and 3 - 17 round mags.
Must be recent production model (between OCT 2012 to present).
Ejector code must be stamped 30274.
Recoil spring assembly must be stamped 0-2-4 or 0-4-3.
Even trade across. If you have extra hi cap mags, I can trade ammo for it.

Location: Fort Smith area only please.
Text only, no emails or PMs please.
REDACTED.

The reason for the 30274 ejector and RSA, is because as before with the previous old ejector 336 and RSA, spent casings were known for ejecting onto the shooter's face, erratic ejection issues, failure to feeds, failure to extract, and stovepipes. It has happened to me before with previous Gen 3 and older Gen 4 models with 336 ejectors. Current RSAs has a bushing at the end of the recoil spring assembly. With previous older RSAs, the recoil springs wraps around to the face of the RSA.

title: For Sale:  **REDUCED** 1861 Civil War Leige F&T Percussion Musket
location: Lansing and all surrounding areas., Lansing, Michigan
postcontent: I have for sale a Liege F & T 1861 Musket - This imported musket is marked on the lock plate “LIEGE / F & T/ 1861” and also a crown over “H” and is marked on the barrel. This is the firm of Falisse and Trapman in Belgium which produced these 1842 French style muskets so heavily used by both Union and Confederate troops. The left-hand side of the stock near the butt is marked in a few locations with more letters, but they are kind of hard to make out. The slotted screws are all market with an H proof mark. The barrel is 40 1/2 inches long, and is a large caliber with a smooth bore. There is a bayonet lug present on the underside of the barrel. The ramrod is present, and is of a tapered style. The trigger guard plate has two ribs as part of its design. This gun was made as a percussion gun. This is an amazing piece of history and anyone in the market should take a good look at what I am offering.
